#import "template.typ": *

#let metadata = (
  title: "Area Solo Suitability Assessment and E13 Formal Assessment",
  unit: "Group A (3-Axis) | Phase 3 — Lesson 5 | Decision Gate + E13",
  author: "C.Moroney",
  version: "v1.0.0",
)

#let lesson = (
title: [Area Solo Suitability Assessment and E13 Formal Assessment]

,aim: [
Demonstrate all Phase 3 elements to S or C standard in a connected student-planned flight, meet the second S standard requirement for both E14a and E14b, confirm E9 and E10 competency, and complete the formal E13 assessment — confirming readiness for unsupervised training area solo operations.
]

,overview: [
This lesson is the area solo suitability assessment and E13 formal assessment. It combines all Phase 3 competency confirmations into a single connected flight planned and conducted by the student as PIC. The instructor is an observer throughout — no coaching or prompting is provided for any assessed item.

This flight counts as the second S standard flight for both E14a (Precautionary Search) and E14b (Forced Landing Without Power). The assessment flight therefore must include both a precautionary search scenario and an engine failure simulation (instructor calls "engine failure" during the training area transit). E9 and E10 have been confirmed in Lessons 9 and 11 respectively; any NC result from those checks is addressed through instructor-inserted remediation flights before this lesson proceeds.

The E13 formal assessment is continuous throughout the complete flight. If all requirements are met at the conclusion of this flight, area solo is authorised.
]

,learning_outcomes: [
No new learning outcomes — this is a milestone assessment and decision gate.
]

,theory_knowledge: [
- Consolidation of all Phase 3 reading
- Theory exam completion confirmed or a solid plan to complete remaining exams
]

,ground_brief_topics: [
Total time: 25 minutes \
Equipment required: Student training record, VNC, NAIPS access, ERSA \

*Student Plans and Briefs the Complete Flight* (20 minutes)
- NAIPS TAF/GAF/GPWT obtained and interpreted; conditions assessed; brief presented to instructor
- NOTAMs checked; relevant items identified
- Maintenance release reviewed; brief presented to instructor
- ERSA: YSPT elevation, CTAF, circuit direction, runway, non-standard items; frequency loaded as standby
- VNC: training area boundaries, candidate FLWOP fields, candidate PSL areas all identified and briefed
- Route: departure, training area entry, element sequence (E9 check, then E14a PSL scenario, then E14b FLWOP, then E16 UA recovery — in a logical order given altitude and time), return to aerodrome, join, circuit and landing
- HASSELL minimum heights for E9 and E10/E16 exercises; FLWOP go-around height stated
- EFATO plan for today's runway and conditions
- Theory exam status: student confirms which exams are complete

*Assessment Criteria Brief* (5 minutes)
- Instructor confirms this is an assessment and decision gate — no coaching or prompting will be provided for any assessed item
- E14a: this flight is the second S standard flight for the precautionary search; the instructor will introduce a weather deterioration scenario at an unannounced point during the training area transit
- E14b: this flight is the second S standard flight for FLWOP; the instructor will call "engine failure" at an unannounced point
- E16: S standard assessed; instructor will create an unusual attitude for the student to recover
- E9 and E10: confirmed in earlier lessons; any NC items must be remediated before this lesson proceeds
- E13: assessed formally across the complete flight
]

,ground_tasks:[
#text(size:12pt)[*Student leads all pre-flight administration completely independently.*]

#text(size:12pt)[*Instructor*]
- Confirms all pre-conditions are met before the flight proceeds (see standards section)
- Receives full brief; may ask clarifying questions
- Confirms conditions are suitable for all planned exercises
- Provides no content input from this point
- Begins recording E13 competency variable assessments from engine start
]

,in_flight_tasks:[
#text(size:12pt)[*Complete Assessment Flight — Student as PIC, Instructor as Silent Assessor*]
The instructor does not coach, prompt, or intervene except for safety. All E13 and element assessments are recorded simultaneously throughout.

_E13 assessment is continuous throughout the complete flight:_

Student conducts the planned sequence:
- Startup, taxi, all radio calls from engine start; transponder set correctly before taxi; squawk ALT once airborne
- Takeoff, departure: circuit departure per AC91-10; correct procedure and call
- Area departure call; training area boundaries monitored verbally throughout
- Active listening maintained; student verbalises traffic picture from radio calls and visual scan

_Training area sequence:_
- *E9 confirmation*: Student-led HASSELL; student-led steep turns (45° and 60°); instructor observes silently; recorded separately
- *E14a (PSL) — second S standard flight*: At an unannounced point, instructor states "the ceiling has dropped to 1200 ft AGL and is still dropping"; student applies ADM aloud; makes precautionary search decision; selects field or alternate; conducts inspection passes; states landing/reject decision with reasoning
- *E14b (FLWOP) — second S standard flight*: At an unannounced point, instructor calls "engine failure"; student executes complete ABCDEF sequence from memory; FLWOP circuit; go-around at pre-briefed training height
- *E16*: At an unannounced point, instructor creates an unusual attitude; student detects and recovers correctly
- Inbound call at 5–10 NM; join; correct procedure
- Circuit and landing
- Simulated radio failure (instructor's discretion): student confirms failure; transmits blind; squawks 7600; states subsequent actions

#text(size:12pt)[*Instructor Assessment*]
- Records S, C, or NC for each element with brief notes
- Records S, C, or NC for each E13 competency variable throughout the flight
- Does not coach, prompt, or intervene except for safety
- If student cannot make a decision and safety is at risk: intervenes, resolves, records the event
]

,common_errors:[
- *Element-specific errors*: Refer to common errors in each Phase 3 lesson plan for remediation guidance.
- *HASSELL omitted before E9 check*: NC for E9 check — non-negotiable.
- *Nose-low recovery — backpressure before wings level*: NC for E16.
- *Radio omissions during transitions*: Most commonly missed are inbound calls — E13 assessed items.
- *ERSA items not briefed before departure*: NC for E13.
]

,post_flight:[
- *Student Leads Debrief* (15 min): Student reviews the complete flight; self-assesses each element and each E13 competency variable.
- *Instructor Provides Formal Assessment Results* (15 min):
  - Element results: S, C, or NC for each with specific comments and evidence
  - E13 formal assessment: S, C, or NC for each competency variable with specific evidence
  - NC items: explain exactly what was observed; agree remediation plan; do not authorise area solo until all NC items are addressed
  - E14a second S standard: confirm whether achieved; record in training record
  - E14b second S standard: confirm whether achieved; record in training record
  - Area solo gate decision: authorised or deferred
  - Theory exam status confirmed
]

,standards_for_progression:[

#text(size:12pt)[*Pre-conditions — all must be confirmed before this lesson proceeds*]
- ☐ E9 at S standard (confirmed in L9 check) — if NC in L9, remediation flight completed and recorded
- ☐ E10 at S standard (confirmed in L11 check) — if NC in L11, remediation flight completed and recorded
- ☐ E14a (PSL) first S standard flight: L9
- ☐ E14b (FLWOP) first S standard flight: L10
- ☐ E16 at P or higher: L11
- ☐ E15 (IOR) at S standard: L8
- ☐ Conditions suitable: ceiling >3500 ft AGL (E16/E10); smooth air preferred; wind \<25 knots

#text(size:12pt)[*Area Solo Authorisation Requirements — all must be confirmed at conclusion of this lesson*]

_Competency requirements:_
- ☐ E9 (Advanced Turning) at S standard — confirmed in Phase 3 (L9 check)
- ☐ E10 (Scenario Based Stalling) at S standard — confirmed in Phase 3 (L11 check)
- ☐ E14a (Precautionary Search) at S standard on *two separate flights* — L9 and this flight
- ☐ E14b (Forced Landing Without Power) at S standard on *two separate flights* — L10 and this flight
- ☐ E15 (IOR — Training Area Operations) at S standard — L8
- ☐ E16 (Unusual Attitudes and Emergencies) at S standard — this lesson
- ☐ *E13 formal assessment passed* — all competency variables at S or above (assessed this lesson)
- ☐ Pre-Solo Air Legislation Exam passed (required before circuit solo)

_E13 competency variables — all must be at S or above:_
- ☐ ERSA home aerodrome and YSPT alternate correctly interpreted; frequencies briefed and loaded before departure
- ☐ All mandatory and recommended CTAF calls with correct structure and timing without prompting
- ☐ Active listening maintained; traffic picture verbalised throughout
- ☐ Transponder operated correctly throughout
- ☐ Airspace awareness; training area boundaries monitored verbally
- ☐ Radio failure procedure applied correctly without prompting when called
- ☐ MAYDAY format correct; transmitted on Centre without prompting (during FLWOP simulation)
- ☐ Area departure and arrival calls correct; overhead join calls correct

_Weather on the day of area solo:_
- ☐ Crosswind within solo authorisation limit
- ☐ Ceiling >2500 ft AGL
- ☐ Visibility >8 km
- ☐ No significant turbulence, windshear, showers, or convective activity in training area

_Additional area solo conditions:_
- ☐ Valid RAAus Student Pilot Certificate held
- ☐ 15 years of age
- ☐ Minimum 2 hours solo PIC circuit time
- ☐ Maintenance release reviewed and briefed by student before every solo flight

_Area solo self-brief requirements (stated before every area solo):_
- ☐ EFATO plan for today's runway
- ☐ Training area entry/exit procedures

#text(size:12pt)[*Weather decision on area solo day:*]\
All competency requirements met ✓ + All weather conditions met ✓ = ✅ Area solo authorised\
Any competency requirement not met = ❌ Address requirement first\
All competency requirements met ✓ + Weather marginal = ❌ Defer; rebook when conditions allow

- *Outcome*: All elements and E13 competency variables recorded in training record. Area solo authorisation recorded. NC items require remediation before area solo commences.
]

,safety:[
- *Weather*: Ceiling >3000 ft AGL for E10/E16; >2500 ft for all other exercises; smooth air preferred; wind \<25 knots
- *Altitude*: HASSELL minimum heights enforced; FLWOP go-around height confirmed before departure; unusual attitude exercises above 2500 ft AGL
- *Emergency Procedures*: EFATO brief before departure; training go-around height confirmed before flight
- *TEM*:
  - Assessment flight — instructor maintains non-interventionist stance while remaining safety-ready
  - Overhead join: monitor for traffic conflicts; intervene if student is about to descend into conflict
  - Radio failure simulation: student does not actually turn off the radio — brief the simulation distinction before departure
  - MAYDAY simulation: transmit on pre-agreed training frequency; do not use CTAF without coordinating with CFI
  - If student shows significant stress affecting safety: end assessment mode; return to coaching; rebook assessment
]

,homework:[
No new homework for this lesson. If area solo was not authorised due to unmet requirements, identify the specific shortfall and address it before the next flight. If authorised: review the area solo consolidation self-brief template in L13 before the first area solo session.
]
)

